properties.description:
<div><b>Fraser Island – bushfire as at 8.40am Fri 30 Oct</b></div><div></div><div>Queensland Fire and Emergency Services (QFES) crews are aware of a bushfire burning at Fraser Island. The fire, which is burning to the north of Awinya track and Dundubara, is posing no threat to property at this time. Queensland Parks and Wildlife Service crews are monitoring the fire. Nearby residents may be affected by smoke. Residents are asked to close windows and doors and if suffering from a respiratory condition, keep medications close by. Motorists should drive with caution and to conditions. If residents are concerned their property is under threat, they are advised to call Triple Zero (000) immediately. </div>

Firefighters are patrolling the area and strengthening containment lines with the assistance of water bombing aircraft. Smoke is expected to impact the surrounding area for several days. Residents are asked to close windows and doors and if suffering from a respiratory condition, keep medications close by. Motorists should drive with caution. If you are concerned your property is under threat, call Triple Zero (000) immediately.</div></div><div></div>

properties.description:
<div><div><b>PREPARE TO LEAVE: Mareeba bushfire as at 2.50pm Thurs 5 Nov</b></div><div><b></b></div><div><b>Bushfire warning level: WATCH AND ACT</b></div><div></div><div>Queensland Fire and Emergency Services (QFES) advises there is a bushfire in Mareeba and surrounding areas and conditions could get worse.</div><div></div><div>You need to <b>be ready to follow your bushfire survival plan</b>. If you do not have a plan, or intend to leave, you should <b>be ready to leave the area because the situation could get worse quickly.</b></div><div></div><div>Currently as at 2.50pm Thursday 5 November a large bushfire is burning in inaccessible land between Godfrey Road and Hastie Road, Mareeba. </div><div></div><div>Residents in Rise Country Estate and Emerald Falls Estate need to prepare to leave.</div><div></div><div>Be advised Queensland Police Service (QPS) have closed Emerald End Road due to smoke.</div><div></div><div>Fire crews are working to contain the fire, with aerial support but firefighters may not be able to protect every property. You <b>should not expect a firefighter at your door.</b></div><div></div><div>People in the area will be affected by smoke, which will reduce visibility and air quality.</div><div></div><div>Call Triple Zero (000) immediately if you believe your property is under threat.</div></div><div></div>
Response Time: 20201105104733
